[SN]TITLE[SN]
Handgun used in Newport betting shop armed robbery

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A silver handgun was used in an armed robbery at a Newport betting shop on Saturday night, police have said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Gwent Police described it as "extremely distressing" for staff at Betfred on Caerleon Road, but said nobody was seriously injured.
The robbery happened at 21:20 BST, with a man in his 40s making off with cash from the till.
Officers are looking for a white man of medium to stocky build who was wearing a dark-coloured hooded top.
